caption: Always delicious!!!!

I thought the place was cool. Definitely had a local Mom & Pop vibe. 3 people working when I visited so my order took  about 45 min, which is the longest I've waited for fish. I expected a Catfish fillet & instead got these pieces, which flavor wise was pretty decent. Problem for me was I'm from NY, but my roots in the deep South & I like my fish fried hard. Everywhere I went in Baltimore, soggy fish seemed to be the norm, & yes I still prefer a fillet. The collards were okay, a lil sweet for my palette, but the Mac & cheese & cornbread were on point. I get the feeling, If I lived around there & visited more often, they could accommodate me on certain requests. This was my first time there & I'd not only return for myself, but recommend to others going to Baltimore. I'd try other menu items as well as get them to fry my next order of fish hard. Overall, a good experience. 👍🏿

Got the SweetPeaz Po Boy and it completely blew me away! My roommate has been raving about this place for awhile so I finally decided to give it a try and I think I've handsdown found my new favorite place to eat in Fed Hill!

The food here is always amazing! I usually come here often because it never disappoints. I'm thoroughly convinced that everything on their menu is AMAZING! I tried to get something low key and simple like fried shrimp as a light snack... don't make the same mistake I did because they don't hold back! I got so much jumbo shrimp that I could barely finish it. WELL WELL WELL worth the price.  The server suggested I get some gravy for the side of rice I had and it was 10000% a game changer. Highly highly recommend doing that as well. If you're reading this review and hesitating please do yourself a favor and grab a plate. You will not be dissapointed.
